  QtLua-Extras - Dependencies
  ===========================

If you want to build yourself QtLua-Extras then you need to install some third-party libraries.

Follow the next steps in order to start with the build instruction.

1. Qt (Mandatory)
-----------------

Make sure you have an installed version of Qt 4.x or Qt 5.x.

Linux users may use any package manager to perform an easy installation.

Mac OS X can use package managers such as Homebrew (http://brew.sh) or MacPorts (http://www.macports.org) in order to have an easy installation.

If you prefer to install from source, download it from http://qt-project.org/downloads.

Make sure to have at least version 4.6.3 installed.


2. Lua (Mandatory)
------------------

Lua is available at: http://www.lua.org.

Make sure to have at least version 5.2 installed.


3. QtLua (Mandatory)
--------------------

QtLua is available from http://www.nongnu.org/libqtlua.

Make sure to have at least version 2.0 installed.


For more information on QtLua-Extras, please, visit its main web page at: https://trac.dpi.inpe.br/qtlua-extras.


